# AI Coding Rules — My SaaS App

## Git
- Branch: feature/{YYMMDD}-{description}
- Commit: {type}({scope}): {description}
- Never commit to main/master/develop
- Never: rebase, force push, auto-resolve conflicts

## Code Architecture
- Frontend: hooks + React Query pattern (no direct fetch)
- Backend: Controller → Service → Repository
- No hardcoded secrets, no PII in logs
- No eslint-disable, no @ts-ignore

## Security
- R0 (auto): local, narrow, reversible
- R1 (ask): reversible but costly
- R2 (block): data loss, external state change
- STRIDE check on new features

## Workflow
- Plan Mode for: bug fixes, features, API changes
- Auto-execute: reads, searches, lint, tests
- Agent order: planner → builder → reviewer
